Gymcom.name: INCLINE BENCH PRESS
Gymcom.explain: An incline bench press allows you to move the back support upwards at an angle to target your chest, biceps, and shoulders.

Gymcom.name: DECLINE BENCH PRESS
Gymcom.explain: When you use a decline bench press, you will target your triceps, shoulders, abs, and pectoral muscles. It allows you to isolate certain areas and focus on hypertrophy.

Gymcom.name: ADJUSTABLE BENCH
Gymcom.explain: Using an adjustable bench, you activate your pectorals, back, triceps, shoulders, and other supporting muscles.

Gymcom.name: CABLE ROW MACHINE
Gymcom.explain: This is a machine that allows you to do compound exercises. When working out, you sit on a padded seat and pull onto handles, which are attached to a cable, and the cable moves the weights.

Gymcom.name: FRONT PULL DOWN MACHINE
Gymcom.explain: This machine causes you to sit on a seat with a pad in front of you and pull down two handles attached to weights that work your latissimus dorsi.

Gymcom.name: ABDOMINAL BENCH
Gymcom.explain: Abs, internal obliques, quadriceps, and transverse abdominal muscles.

Gymcom.name: SEATED CALF MACHINE
Gymcom.explain: gastrocnemius, tibialis posterior, peroneal, and soleus.

Gymcom.name: DUMBBELLS
Gymcom.explain: Dumbells can target every muscle in your body
